article.headline: Oral Roberts beats Texas state 82-65
article.story: TULSA, Okla. -- Obi Emegano scored 27 points and his team sank 10 3-pointers on Saturday as Oral Roberts handily defeated Texas State 82-65. The Golden Eagles (2-1) shot 66.7 percent from three-point range in making 10 of 15 tries. Emegano had four 3-pointers. Shawn Glover scored 18 points, including two 3-pointers, Korey Billbury added 14 points with three 3-pointers and DJ Jackson scored 11 points, with two 3-pointers. The Bobcats (0-3) kept the game close until Glover hit a 3-pointer with 10:54 to play in the first quarter, giving Oral Roberts a 13-10 lead and sparking an 11-point run. The Golden Eagles led 30-24 at the half, then steadily pulled away. Emani Gant led Texas State with 14 points. The teams have faced off five times and ORU holds a 4-1 advantage in the series.
